# roleflow.word — what a ROLEFLOW is, a conditional word. A being's quality, the word that gives
# it its role each moment. Descends from word.word, can.word, role.word, being.word, the verbs.
# The host eval loop is seed/present/roles/roleFlow.js. A roleflow is pure: same moment, same role.
# `pass`, `play`, `stack`, `test` are grounded here, the conditional's verbs. This is the Word's
# colon at home, a when then a role.

A roleflow is a being's quality, the conditional word that gives it its role.
A roleflow has clauses, in order. A clause has a role, and may have a when.
A when tests the moment, the caller, verb, act, space, time, and the being, by equals, in, more, less, or present, with and, or, not.
A clause with no when always passes. A clause with one passes only when its when is true.
When a clause passes, the clause gives its role only if the role asks no cognition, or the cognition it asks is the being's. Otherwise the clause is skipped and the flow goes on.
When a being is granted a role whose words can in this space, or the role is a seed its nature has: the being can play it.
The first passing clause that does not stack is the primary. A clause that stacks gives its words on top of the primary, not in its place.
A roleflow folds to one role, the primary's name and voice with the words of all that stack.
A caller may name a role when it calls. When the being can play it, it is the primary, and the flow gives only what stacks.
When no clause gives a primary, the being's default role is the primary. When none can, there is no primary role. The fold yields only what stacks, or nothing.
The role a roleflow folds is the moment's, signed into its act.
A roleflow is a pure word. The same moment folds the same role.
